#. type: Title #
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`StopOnError` - stop validation on the first error"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
msgid ""
"This rule applies to a group of rules and allows you to stop the validation "
"for the whole group immediately after an error occurs in any of the rules. "
"This means that all rules following the rule that failed validation won't be "
"run at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
msgid ""
"This can be useful for performance-intensive validations, such as database "
"queries or some complex calculations.  The order of rules within a group is "
"crucial here - the \"lightweight\" rules need to be placed above the "
"\"heavy\" ones:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Length;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\StopOnError;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Validator;\n"
"\n"
"$data = 2;\n"
"$rule = new StopOnError([\n"
"    new Length(min: 3), // \"Lightweight\" rule, will be run and won't pass the validation.\n"
"    new MyHeavyRule(), // \"Heavy\" rule, won't be run at all because of the existing error.\n"
"]);\n"
"$result = (new Validator())->validate($data, $rule);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
msgid ""
"When using with other rules and conditional validation, it behaves like a "
"single unit. For example, with default settings it will not be skipped if "
"the previous rule didn't pass the validation. To change this behavior, set "
"`$skipOnError` to `true`. This allows to use it for limiting the list of "
"errors per property to just the first one (in HTML forms, for example)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$rules = [\n"
"    'property1' => new SimpleRule1(), // Let's say there is an error.\n"
"    // Then this rule is skipped completely with all its related rules because `skipOnError` is set to `true`. Useful\n"
"    // when all rules within `StopOnError` are heavy.\n"
"    'property2' => new StopOnError(\n"
"        [\n"
"            new HeavyRule1(), // Skipped.\n"
"            new HeavyRule2(), // Skipped.\n"
"        ],\n"
"        skipOnError: true,\n"
"    ),\n"
"    // This rule is not skipped because `skipOnError` is `false` by default. Useful for forcing validation and\n"
"    // limiting the errors.\n"
"    'property3' => new StopOnError([\n"
"        new SimpleRule2(), // Assuming there is another error.\n"
"        new SimpleRule3(), // Skipped.\n"
"    ]),\n"
"    // Skipping of other intermediate rules depends on `skipOnError` option set in these intermediate rules.\n"
"    'property4' => new SimpleRule4(), // Not skipped, because `skipOnError` is `false` by default.\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-stop-on-error.md
msgid ""
"Use grouping / ordering / `skipOnError` option to achieve the desired effect."
msgstr ""
